All **6 tests pass**, zero TypeScript errors. No plumbing changes were needed — the existing recursive descent parser's `while` loop in `parseExpression()` already chains arbitrarily many `+` operators left-associatively, and the generator tracks stdin token indices sequentially across all terms:

```js
// Generated for "read<U8>() + read<U8>() + read<U8>()" with input "1 2 3":
const tokens = stdIn.trim().split(/\s+/);
return (((Math.floor(Number(tokens[0])) & 0xFF) 
       + (Math.floor(Number(tokens[1])) & 0xFF)) 
       + (Math.floor(Number(tokens[2])) & 0xFF));
// → ((1 + 2) + 3) = 6 ✓
